canonical:
  title: 少日
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 少日豪談奮兩髯年來斂鍔遠人嫌從前宦路羊膓險抵老才名鼠尾尖詩不驚人吟又改酒能忘我醉還添欲書折簡招碁伴凍筆如錐不可拈
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 少日
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 少日豪談奮兩髯。年來斂鍔遠人嫌。從前宦路羊膓險。抵老才名鼠尾尖。詩不驚人吟又改。酒能忘我醉還添。欲書折簡招碁伴。凍筆如錐不可拈。
korean:
  title: 소일
  author: 서거정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    젊을 때에는 호기롭게 말탈 때 두 수염을 떨쳤더니
    요새 와서는 칼날을 거두어 남의 꺼림 멀리한다
    지금까지의 벼슬 길은 양의 창자 험했는데
    늙어지매 재주의 이름은 쥐 꼬리가 뾰족하네
    시가 사람을 놀라게 하지 못하매 읊어 보고는 또 고치고
    술은 나를 잊게 하매 취하고도 또 마신다
    절간을 써서 바둑 친구를 부르려 하나
    언 붓이 송곳 같아서 집을 수가 없구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1430_010_0070&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: In My Youth
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In my youth I spoke with swagger, my whiskers trembling with pride.
    Now in my years I've sheathed my blade—distant from the world's disdain.
    The path of office wound like a sheep's intestine, treacherous and steep,
    and age has worn my talents to a rat's tail, sharp but thin.
    My verses fail to stir the heart, so I revise them as I recite,
    while wine lets me forget myself—I drink again though drunk.
    I wish to write a note inviting friends to play at chess,
    but my frozen brush has turned to an awl—I cannot hold it in my hand.
  footnotes:
    - The 'sheep's intestine' refers to the winding, precarious path of official service in the bureaucracy.
    - The 'rat's tail' is a Chinese idiom expressing something small, insignificant, or diminished—here referring to the author's faded reputation and talent in old age.
    - The final image of the frozen brush suggests both the literal difficulty of writing in winter and the metaphorical loss of the poet's creative power with age.
